# Reflect

## Stage Goal

Capture what was learned so future frontend work and generated templates improve.

## Inputs Needed

- Completed work summary.
- Test and review results.
- User or reviewer feedback.
- Repeated friction, missing rules, or unclear generated instructions.

## AI Behavior Expected

- Record what worked.
- Record what failed or slowed the work.
- Identify missing frontend template guidance.
- Create follow-up tasks or research notes.
- Update `.ai/rules/` or `.ai/skills/` recommendations when repeated issues appear.

## AI Behavior Forbidden

- Turning reflection into vague praise.
- Recording lessons without actions.
- Reopening settled decisions without new evidence.
- Expanding scope into unrelated domains.

## Output Expected

- What worked.
- What failed.
- Template gaps.
- Follow-up tasks.
- Rejected or deferred ideas, if any.

## Quality Bar

Reflect is complete when future work has a concrete improvement path or a recorded reason not to revisit a decision.
